<div id="bulkArtworkStep" class="centerInner" style="display:none;">
    <div id="artworkStep1" class="artworkStep clear">
        <div id="artworkButtonLeft" class="artworkStepButton selected" onclick="firstTimeOrder()">
            This Is My First Time Ordering
        </div>
        <div id="artworkButtonRight" class="artworkStepButton" onclick="preExistingOrder()">
            I have Ordered With This Logo Before
        </div>
        <div id="uploadArtworkHolder">            
            <div>
                <p><b>Please Upload Your Artwork</b></p>
                <p><input type="file" id="bulkArtwork" /></p> 
                <p><b>1 FILE MAX</b> - Additional files can be emailed after your order is placed.</p>
            </div>
            <div id="artworkNew">
                <div id="artworkGuidelines">
                    <p>Please upload an image of the artwork you would like us to convert to use on your hats.</p>
                    <p>We will convert and digitize your artwork. You will receive mockups and stitching proofs for approval and feedback before your hats are stitched.</p>
                    <p>Orders are submitted as standard 2D embroirdery. 3D Puff embroidery is an extra $5 per hat and is only possible on some designs and is billed separately.</p>
                    <p style="color:red;"><i>Please keep in mind that really small details do not work well for embroidery. Very small text and details will need to be removed from some designs. <b>LESS IS MORE</b> when it comes to embroidery designs.</i></p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div id="artworkExisting" style="display:none;">
                <p>Please upload an image to help us locate and verify your artwork we have setup previously. We will assign your pre-existing artwork file to your order.</p>
            </div>
        </div><!--/uploadArtworkHolder-->
    </div><!--/ArtworkStep1-->

    <div id="artworkStep2Header" class="artworkStepHeader clear">
        Artwork Placement
    </div>
    <div id="artworkStep2" class="artworkStep">
        <h2>Select where would you like the artwork placed.<br/>
                                                           <span style="font-weight:normal; font-size:12px;">Our standard sizing for Centered designs is 2.5" tall and 4.2" wide (when possible). Offset designs will be a maximum 2.5" tall and 3.2" wide. If you would like different dimensions and your artwork will work for it, please let us know in the order notes. The maximum embroidery field size is 6.5" wide by 2.5" tall. Designs are Limited to 11,000 stitches. 90% of designs fall into this range under our default sizing. Any designs that go beyond this require $1 extra per 1,000 stitches.</span>
        </h2>
        <div id="placementSelect">
            <div class="placementOption" id="left" onclick="$('#artPlacement').text('left');$('.placementOption#left').addClass('selected');$('.placementOption#right').removeClass('selected');$('.placementOption#center').removeClass('selected');">
                <img src="~/Images/LeftPlacement.jpg" class="placementImage" />
            </div>
            <div class="placementOption" id="center" onclick="$('#artPlacement').text('center');$('.placementOption#left').removeClass('selected');$('.placementOption#right').removeClass('selected');$('.placementOption#center').addClass('selected');">
                <img src="~/Images/CenterPlacement.jpg" class="placementImage" />
            </div>
            <div class="placementOption" id="right" onclick="$('#artPlacement').text('right');$('.placementOption#left').removeClass('selected');$('.placementOption#right').addClass('selected');$('.placementOption#center').removeClass('selected');">
                <img src="~/Images/RightPlacement.jpg" class="placementImage" />
            </div>
            <span id="artPlacement" style="display:none;"></span>
        </div>
    </div><!--/ArtworkStep2-->

    <div id="artworkStep3Header" class="artworkStepHeader clear">
        Thread Colors
    </div>
    <div id="artworkStep3" class="artworkStep">
        <h2>
            These are the thread colors we use:<br />
            <span style="font-weight:normal; font-size:12px;">Different screens can display colors differently. Colors are more vibrant in person. We only use high quality Madeira 100% polyester thread.</span>
        </h2>

        @{ Html.RenderPartial("~/Views/Bulk/ThreadColorChart.cshtml"); }

        <div class="clear">
            <h2>
                Color changes in your design are allowed in quantities of 6 or more.<br />
                <span style="font-weight:normal; font-size:12px;"><b>For Example:</b> 6 Black Hats: Red Stitching / 6 White Hats: Black Stitching</span>
            </h2>
        </div>

        <div id="itemColorList">

        </div>


        <div class="clear">
            <h2>
                Please tell us any specific instructions or details about your order that you think we should know.<br />
                <span style="font-weight:normal; font-size:12px;"><b>For Example:</b> If you ordered black hats and the text in your logo is black tell us what color stitching to use. Also, list out the colors of stitching you want on the different color hats you may have selected. (1 Color Combination per 6 or more hats allowed)</span>
            </h2>
            <div>
                <textarea class="productDetailsTextMulti textBoxMulti" id="txtDetails" placeholder="Order Notes" rows="10"></textarea>
            </div>
        </div>

    </div><!--/ArtworkStep3-->

    <div id="artworkStep4Header" class="artworkStepHeader clear">
        Back Stitching
    </div>
    <div id="artworkStep4" class="artworkStep">
        <h2>
            Add Back Stitching (Text Only - Available for orders > 6)<br />
            <span style="font-weight:normal; font-size:12px;">Back stitching is $5 per hat. Please add what text you want added to the back of the hats. Limited to the same text on all hats.</span>
        </h2>
        <div id="backStitching">
            <div id="chkBackHolder" onclick="toggleBackStitching()"><input type="checkbox" id="chkBackStitching" onclick="toggleBackStitching()" /> Back Stitching</div>
            <input type="text" placeholder="Back Stitching Details" id="txtBackStitching" />
        </div>
        <div id="rightSideStitching" class="hidden">
            <div id="chkRightHolder" onclick="toggleRightSideStitching()"><input type="checkbox" id="chkRightSideStitching" onclick="toggleRightSideStitching()" /> Right Side Stitching</div>
            <input type="text" placeholder="Right Side Stitching Details" id="txtRightSideStitching" />
        </div>
        <div id="leftSideStitching" class="hidden">
            <div id="chkLeftHolder" onclick="toggleLeftSideStitching()"><input type="checkbox" id="chkLeftSideStitching" onclick="toggleLeftSideStitching()" /> Left Side Stitching</div>
            <input type="text" placeholder="Left Side Stitching Details" id="txtLeftSideStitching" />
        </div>
    </div><!--/ArtworkStep4-->





    <div id="designProcessExplained">

    </div>
</div><!--/bulkArtworkStep-->
